cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on pruning deep models for image classification tasks on ImageNet-2012 dataset. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning approach for model compression. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with AutoML (Automated Machine Learning) for model pruning. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper involves neural networks and their compression. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on data structures or algorithms, but rather on model compression techniques.
